"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450614","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-09","<p>Since 2005 the Ministry of Defence has received around £117 million in disposal receipts from the sale of surplus sites in Northern Ireland.</p><p>All transactions were carried out in accordance with the Hillsborough Agreement.</p><p>Over the same period, the Department gifted four bases to the Northern Ireland Executive with an estimated total combined value of £21 million. As outlined in a Written Ministerial Statement (HCWS509) released on 4 February 2016, there is also intent to gift an additional 59 surplus Service Family Accommodation units to the Northern Ireland Executive, with a combined value of £3.5 million.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2016-02-09T16:54:58.603Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450614/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450614/answer","20160204_WMS_Gifting_of_Surplus_Accommodation_to_the_Northern_Ireland_Excecutive.docx","WMS on Gifting Accommodation to NI Executive","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450614/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-04","Military Bases: Northern Ireland","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how much money has been received from the sale of former military sites and bases in Northern Ireland to date.","false","Biography information for Lord Browne of Belmont",,"Lord Browne of Belmont","HL5915"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450615","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-02-23","<p>Since 2010, UK Trade and Investment (UKTI) and Enterprise Ireland have organised a joint trade mission to the Singapore Air Show in February 2014.</p><p>Her Majesty’s Government is committed to helping UK business succeed overseas, including in the Republic of Ireland where UKTI is represented and is actively promoting trade and investment between our two countries.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p>",,"Lord Maude of Horsham",,"2016-02-23T12:30:02.74Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450615/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450615/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450615/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-02-04","Trade Missions","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what joint trade missions have been undertaken by the UK and the Republic of Ireland since 2010.","false","Biography information for Lord Browne of Belmont",,"Lord Browne of Belmont","HL5916"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450616","Home Office","false","2016-02-17","<p>We believe approximately 800 UK linked individuals have travelled to take part in the conflict in Syria and Iraq since it began. Many have joined Daesh and other terrorist groups. We cannot provide specific data on how many nationals have travelled to Libya or other countries on national security grounds.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2016-02-17T14:56:19.407Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450616/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450616/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450616/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-02-04","Terrorism: British Nationals Abroad","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what estimate they have made of the number of UK nationals who have travelled to participate in terrorist-related activity in (1) Syria, (2) Iraq, (3) Libya, and (4) another country, from 2013 to date.","false","Biography information for Lord Browne of Belmont",,"Lord Browne of Belmont","HL5917"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450617","Home Office","false","2016-02-12","<p>The information requested is shown in the following table. The figures are based on the number of civil penalties issued to individual employers during each of the last four complete financial years and the current financial year to 31st January 2016. This includes public and private limited companies, sole traders, partnerships and franchises.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial year</p></td><td><p>Civil penalties issued</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>14</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>19</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>42</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>85</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16 (to 31<sup>st</sup> January 2016)</p></td><td><p>57</p></td></tr></tbody></table>",,"Lord Bates",,"2016-02-12T14:07:33.897Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450617/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450617/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450617/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-02-04","Undocumented Workers: Northern Ireland","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many business establishments in Northern Ireland have been fined for employing illegal national workers in each of the last four years.","false","Biography information for Lord Browne of Belmont",,"Lord Browne of Belmont","HL5918"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450618","Home Office","false","2016-02-11","<p>The Government is committed to ensuring that young people are protected and treated appropriately while in police custody. This is why in January last year, the Home Secretary commissioned a multi-agency Working Group on Section 38(6) of the Police and Criminal Evidence Act 1984, which concerns the transfer of children from police custody to local authority care when charged and denied bail. The purpose of the group is to better understand the problems with the operation of the law and to develop solutions to enable forces and local authorities to meet their respective statutory responsibilities. The group is currently finalising a package of measures and will present these to the Home Secretary once the work is complete.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2016-02-11T15:07:58.303Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450618/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450618/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450618/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-02-04","Police Custody: Children","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what action they are taking to prevent children being detained in police cells overnight because no suitable local authority accommodation is available.","false","Biography information for Lord Condon",,"Lord Condon","HL5919"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450619","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-02-29","<p>The Government will be writing to the Higher Education Funding Council (HEFCE) shortly setting out its funding for the coming year. The HEFCE Board will make decisions on funding for universities and colleges in light of the Government’s letter. The Government continues to recognise the importance of language study and the value of studying abroad. Approximately 220,000 students have benefitted from the Erasmus Programme.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Evans of Bowes Park",,"2016-02-29T13:10:56.457Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450619/answer","Biography information for Baroness Evans of Bowes Park","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450619/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450619/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-04","Languages: Higher Education","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they will take steps to encourage the Higher Education Funding Council for England to continue supporting language study, in particular by maintaining the Year Abroad subsidy.","false","Biography information for Baroness Coussins",,"Baroness Coussins","HL5920"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450620","Home Office","false","2016-02-19","<p>The National Crime Agency is responsible for the assessment of threats, including methods of trafficking by criminals. Information on this is not centrally recorded on the National Referral Mechanism (NRM). Data included in NRM referral forms concentrates on detail specifically required to prove the three constituent elements of human trafficking. This would not necessarily include the detail required to assess methodology used to re-traffick victims and as such does not form part of assessment reporting. The independent evaluation of the trial by the University of Bedfordshire collected data on the number of all potentially trafficked children referred to the trial, along with their characteristics including age, gender and geographical location, as well as the number of children that were recorded as missing. However the evaluation did not collect data on the number of children in the trial that were re-trafficked and it is not possible to determine how many of those children who went missing were subsequently re-trafficked.</p>",,"Lord Bates","HL5922 ; HL5923","2016-02-19T12:41:53.033Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450620/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450620/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450620/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-02-04","Human Trafficking: Children","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of how many suspected child victims of modern slavery were subsequently re-trafficked after being referred to the National Referral Mechanism in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Baroness Doocey",,"Baroness Doocey","HL5921"
