"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450797","Home Office","false","2016-02-09","<p>The UK has already committed to resettling 20,000 refugees from the region during this parliament through the Syrian Vulnerable Persons Resettlement scheme, and we have no plans to increase this at the present time.</p><p>Resettlement is only one strand of our efforts in the region, and is complemented by the UK’s significant humanitarian aid programme, and our diplomatic efforts to end the conflict. We believe this approach is the best way to ensure that the UK’s help has the greatest impact for the majority of refugees who remain in the region and their host countries.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2016-02-09T17:00:31.58Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450797/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450797/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450797/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-02-04","Refugees: Syria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if the Prime Minister will increase the Government's commitment beyond 20,000 on the number of Syrian refugees it plans to offer asylum to.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","25984"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450798","Department for International Development","false","2016-02-09","<p>The purpose of coalition airstrikes against Daesh is to degrade its ability to project military force within Syria and Iraq, which is one source of displacement as non-combatants flee from Daesh’s sphere of influence. Coalition airstrikes have been proceeding since September 2014. Coalition partners do all they can to minimise the risks of civilian impact of coalition military action in line with international law.</p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2016-02-09T17:38:26.957Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450798/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450798/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450798/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-02-04","Syria: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, if the Prime Minister will make an assessment of the number of people in Syria who have been displaced as a result of UK military intervention in that country.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","25991"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450799","Scotland Office","false","2016-02-11","<p>I have met separately with local authorities in Dundee, Angus and Perth and I was able to confirm that the UK Government is interested to hear from any local authority or group of local authorities interested in pursuing a City Deal. To date, we have not received formal proposals from any of those Councils.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2016-02-11T12:00:40.5Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450799/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450799/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450799/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2016-02-04","Local Government: Dundee","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what discussions he has had with Cabinet colleagues on the City Deal for Dundee and neighbouring authorities; and when the Government plans to make a decision on that deal.","false","Biography information for Chris Law","Dundee West","Chris Law","25898"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450800","Department for Transport","false","2016-02-09","<p>The British Transport Police Authority has set an expected budget of £295.1 million for the British Transport Police in 2016/17.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-02-09T11:32:50.273Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450800/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450800/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450800/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-04","British Transport Police: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 3 February 2016 to Question 24232 from the hon. Member for Dewsbury and Mirfield, what budget has been set for the British Transport Police for 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","25975"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450801","Department for Transport","false","2016-02-09","<p>I can confirm that my officials have discussed improvements to Luton station with Network Rail recently. Luton station has been selected for a number of DfT funded improvements, including Access for All and the National Stations Improvement Programme.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-02-09T17:02:43.89Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450801/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450801/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450801/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-04","Luton Station","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent discussions his Department has had with Network Rail on improvements to Luton station.","false","Biography information for Mr Gavin Shuker","Luton South","Mr Gavin Shuker","25868"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450802","Department for Transport","false","2016-02-12","<p>There are currently (a) two officials, (b) one further official on secondment to the Department and (c) no contracted workers working on taxi and private hire vehicle policy in the Department for Transport. All work in the Buses and Taxis division. The subject forms one part of the officials’ roles. This level of staffing for work on taxis and private hire vehicles is essentially consistent with that going back to 2009/10.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","25871","2016-02-12T13:01:58.637Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450802/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450802/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450802/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-04","Taxis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many (a) officials, (b) other staff and (c) contracted workers in his Department are working on taxi and private hire vehicle policy.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","25870"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450803","Department for Transport","false","2016-02-12","<p>There are currently (a) two officials, (b) one further official on secondment to the Department and (c) no contracted workers working on taxi and private hire vehicle policy in the Department for Transport. All work in the Buses and Taxis division. The subject forms one part of the officials’ roles. This level of staffing for work on taxis and private hire vehicles is essentially consistent with that going back to 2009/10.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","25870","2016-02-12T13:01:58.583Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450803/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450803/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450803/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-04","Taxis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many (a) officials, (b) other staff and (c) contracted workers in his Department are working on licensing of taxi and private hire vehicles in the Buses and Taxis division.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","25871"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450804","Home Office","false","2016-02-11","<p>Common Law Police Disclosure (CLPD) is police led. The National Police Chiefs’ Council issue guidance for CLPD to all Chief Officers to ensure compliance.</p><p>Operational use of the scheme follows the principles of the statutory guidance relating to the disclosure of local police information on criminal record certificates.</p><p>The Home Office does not make any separate assessment of the scheme.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2016-02-11T16:27:26.32Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450804/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450804/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450804/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-02-04","Police: Disclosure of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate her Department has made of the effectiveness of the arrangements for information sharing between police and councils under Common Law Police Disclosure.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","25884"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450805","Department for Transport","false","2016-02-12","<p>As part of our Rail Investment Strategy, the Government is investing over £15 billion in enhancements to the rail network. This includes the modernisation of the Great Western Main Line, and investing £700 million on infrastructure in the most congested routes in London and the South East. In addition, we are delivering the £14.8bn Crossrail and £6.5bn Thameslink projects.</p><p> </p><p>Further, our franchising programme is delivering valuable passenger benefits, such as smart ticketing and faster services.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-02-12T11:37:25.183Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450805/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450805/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450805/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-04","Railways: South of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he is taking to improve rail infrastructure and service in the south of England.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","25849"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450806","Department for Transport","false","2016-02-12","<p>The Department has not made any detailed assessment of the effectiveness of autonomous emergency braking systems, but we are aware that a number of studies have highlighted the potential for a reduction in collisions. Most trucks exceeding 8 tonnes and coaches registered after 1 November 2015 are fitted with it, and we support measures by EuroNCAP to encourage its fitment in new cars.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-02-12T11:42:52.493Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450806/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450806/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450806/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-04","Motor Vehicles: Brakes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of autonomous emergency braking systems in reducing the number of road traffic accidents.","false","Biography information for Adam Afriyie","Windsor","Adam Afriyie","25845"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450807","Department for Transport","false","2016-02-09","<p>I refer the hon Member to the answer I gave on 20 November 2015, <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-11-09/15469/" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-11-09/15469/</a>.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-02-09T17:25:24.087Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450807/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450807/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450807/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-04","Taxis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when he plans to respond to the report by the Law Commission on taxi and private hire services, published in May 2014.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","25928"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450808","Department for Transport","false","2016-02-09","<p>Guidance produced for seafarers in respect of the National Minimum Wage (NMW) is the responsibility of the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills (BIS).</p><p>General NMW guidance, including reference to seafarers, can be found at;</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/calculating-the-minimum-wage" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/calculating-the-minimum-wage</a></p><p> </p><p>BIS is currently in the process of revising its NMW guidance for seafarers (in full consultation with relevant stakeholders) and expects to publish the amended guidance in early 2016.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-02-09T16:03:24.713Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450808/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450808/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450808/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-04","Shipping: Minimum Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 26 January 2016 to Question 24307, if he will publish on his Departmental website the existing guidance produced by his Department for seafarers on the national minimum wage.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","25958"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450809","Department for Transport","false","2016-02-09","<p>I would like to clarify that, in my contribution to the debate in Parliament on 28 January 2016, column 523, I was making a statement about how certain areas of the network in the South East have not been substantially changed or enhanced in keeping with the modern demands being placed upon them since the 1930’s, though evidently renewals will have happened over time.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-02-09T16:55:44.063Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450809/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450809/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450809/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-04","Southeastern: Railway Track","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to the oral contribution of the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Transport of 28 January 2016, Official Report, column 523, on trains running over tracks from the 1930s, which sections of track on which routes carrying Southeastern services date from the 1930s.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","25989"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450810","Department for Transport","false","2016-02-09","<p>The 2015 Spending Review settlement provided to Transport for London already takes into account its likely income from rail fares in 2016 and subsequent years. The Department has no plans to make any further adjustment to TfL’s funding in respect of this matter.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-02-09T14:16:18.483Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450810/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450810/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450810/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-04","Railways: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 2 February 2016 to Question 24776, whether his Department has made or plans to make a financial contribution to Transport for London related to the decision to increase the cost of rail fares in London by the retail price index in 2016.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","25990"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450811","Department for Transport","false","2016-02-09","<p>The Cycle Proofing Working Group met on 14 January 2016. The Department for Transport does not have a Cycling Health sub-group.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-02-09T11:18:47.26Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450811/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450811/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450811/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-04","Cycling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, on what date the (a) Cycle Proofing Working Group and (b) Cycling Health sub-group last met.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","25993"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450812","Department for Transport","false","2016-02-09","<p>The Department’s SR15 settlement includes over £300 million for cycling over the life of this Parliament. There is no specific budget within this funding denoted ‘cycle safety’ since a variety of cycling schemes do and will help in various ways to improve cycle safety. Several projects can however be noted:</p><p> </p><p>- We are providing £50m over the next four years to support Bikeability cycle training in schools; £11m was provided in 2015/16. This funding will help to increase children's road awareness, encourage active travel and improve future motorists’ empathy for more vulnerable road users. We expect to train a further 1 million children with the new funding settlement.</p><p> </p><p>- We are spending £114m from 2015 onwards on the Cycling Ambition Cities programme which will accelerate their development of local cycling networks, including increased protection for cyclists at junctions.</p><p> </p><p>- In addition, through the Road Investment Strategy, Highways England will spend £100m through to 2020/21 to make around 200 locations on our major road network more cycle-friendly.</p><p> </p><p>Much more widely, however, other Government funding streams will also contribute to projects which could deliver improved cycle safety. Through the Local Growth Fund, the Department estimates that an investment of at least £270m is planned by local enterprise partnerships for cycling infrastructure. Local authorities could also use sums from the £1.3bn Integrated Transport Block to 2019/20 for cycle safety schemes.</p><p> </p><p>It should also be noted that spending on road maintenance can benefit not just motorists but can also lead to safer conditions for cyclists, and a record £6.1billion is allocated to local highway authorities between 2015 and 2021 for road maintenance.</p><p> </p><p>Regarding cycleway maintenance, from 2018/19 the plan is to change the formula used to allocate local highways maintenance capital funding so that it also takes into account footways and cycleways as well as the roads, bridges and street lighting, which it is currently based on. Once implemented, around 9% of the funding for local highways maintenance will be based on footway and cycleway lengths.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-02-09T11:28:35.503Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450812/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450812/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450812/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-04","Cycling: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how much funding has been allocated to cycling safety from 2015 to 2020.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","25994"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450813","Department for Transport","false","2016-02-12","<p>On 30 January 2016, there were 28,703 holders of full driving licences in the Wealden constituency postal code areas over the age of 70.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-02-12T11:01:00.84Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450813/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450813/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450813/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-04","Driving: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many holders of full driving licences in Wealden constituency are people aged over 70 who have renewed their licence.","false","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","Wealden","Nusrat Ghani","25967"
