"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450399","Department of Health","false","2016-02-08","<p>Bowel Scope Screening is currently offered in 48 out of 63 screening units with 25% of all general practitioner practices in England engaging with bowel scope.</p><p> </p><p>All screening centres are expected to go live in 2016 and it is hoped that full roll out of bowel scope screening will be achieved by 2019.</p><p> </p><p>The annual population eligible for screening (55 year olds) is approximately 780,000 across all screening centres. This data come from the counts of people turning 55 each year.</p><p> </p><p>Data on screening centres offering bowel scope screening is currently unavailable due to deductive disclosure; however the programme is looking to publish the data as soon as possible.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","25837","2016-02-08T17:50:03.26Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450399/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450399/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450399/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-02-03","Bowel Cancer: Screening","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, when he plans that all eligible individuals will have been invited to participate in the NHS Bowel Scope Screening Programme.","false","Biography information for Mr John Baron","Basildon and Billericay","Mr John Baron","25836"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450400","Department of Health","false","2016-02-08","<p>Bowel Scope Screening is currently offered in 48 out of 63 screening units with 25% of all general practitioner practices in England engaging with bowel scope.</p><p> </p><p>All screening centres are expected to go live in 2016 and it is hoped that full roll out of bowel scope screening will be achieved by 2019.</p><p> </p><p>The annual population eligible for screening (55 year olds) is approximately 780,000 across all screening centres. This data come from the counts of people turning 55 each year.</p><p> </p><p>Data on screening centres offering bowel scope screening is currently unavailable due to deductive disclosure; however the programme is looking to publish the data as soon as possible.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","25836","2016-02-08T17:50:03.337Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450400/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450400/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450400/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-02-03","Bowel Cancer: Screening","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, (a) how many people and (b) what proportion of the eligible population have been invited to participate in the NHS Bowel Scope Screening Programme by screening centre in each year since that programme was launched.","false","Biography information for Mr John Baron","Basildon and Billericay","Mr John Baron","25837"
